{{Proposed deletion/dated |concern = The subject of the article does not appear to be noteable. There seems to be no secondary sources that discuss the subject. |timestamp = 20181202004913 |help = }} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{EngvarB|date=January 2018}} {{unreferenced|date=April 2015}} [[File:Woking-BasingstokeCanal.jpg|right|300px|thumb]] The '''Accessible Boating Association''' is a [[waterway society]] and a [[Charitable organization#Charity registration|registered charity]] number 295034 in [[Hampshire]], England<ref name="ABAHome">{{cite web |title=Accessible Boating Association Home |url=https://www.accessibleboating.org.uk/ |website=Accessible Boating Association |publisher=Accessible Boating Association |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>.
The Association aims to provide [[boating]] opportunities on the [[Basingstoke Canal]] for [[disabled]] people with [[Accessibility|access]] difficulties. The Association was founded in 1985 and was formerly known as "Boats for the Handicapped"<ref name="ABAHistory">{{cite web |title=History of the ABA formerly Boats for the Handicapped Association |url=https://www.accessibleboating.org.uk/history.html |website=Accessible Boating Association |publisher=Accessible Boating Association |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>. It is a member of the [[National Community Boats Association]]<ref name="NCBAABAProfile">{{cite web |title=NCBA Accessible Boating Profile |url=http://national-cba.co.uk/profile/accessibleboating/ |website=National Community Boating Association |publisher=National Community Boating Association |accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>.
The Association's boats have been specially designed to provide facilities for [[disabled]] passengers: *Accommodation for disabled persons and their [[carer]]s *Space for several [[wheelchair]]s *Extra wide ramps for access *[[Hydraulic]] [[elevator|lift]]s *a hospital-type bed for a severely [[handicapped]] person<ref name="ABAHome" />
