[[File:Cannabis ruderalis.jpg|right|thumb|Cannabis in Romania, 2004]]
'''Cannabis in Romania''' is illegal for recreational use and allowed in only limited form for medical use.

Some of the earliest evidence of the psychoactive use of cannabis have been found in Romania, including the archaeological sites of [[Frumușica, Botoșani|Frumușica]] and [[Gurbănești]].<ref>Robert C. Clarke, Mark D. Merlin. ''Cannabis: Evolution and Ethnobotany''. University of California Press, 2013. p. 109</ref>

==Prohibition==
In 1928 Romania established laws for countering narcotics, including hashish and its preparations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.emcdda.europa.eu//html.cfm//index5174EN.html?# |title=EMCDDA &#124; Country legal profiles |publisher=Emcdda.europa.eu |date= |accessdate=2016-11-26}}</ref>

==Medical cannabis==
A limited medical cannabis law was passed in 2013 allowing for the use of low-[[THC]] (below 0.2%) derivatives of the plant only.<ref>{{cite news|title=Romania Legalizes Medical Marijuana, Becomes 10th EU Country To Permit Theraputic Use|url=http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=154315|accessdate=14 October 2013|newspaper=Novinite|date=6 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Gates |first1=Sara |title=Romania To Allow Medicinal Use Of Marijuana Derivatives, But Drug Remains Illegal |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/10/05/romania-medical-marijuana-legal_n_4049658.html |accessdate=24 August 2018 |work=HuffPost |date=5 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Medical Marijuana in Romania |url=https://www.marijuanadoctors.com/international-patients/romania/ |website=marijuanadoctors.com |accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Toea |first1=Diana |title=Marijuana medicinala e legala in Romania. De ce nu avem pe piata niciun medicament pe baza de canabis |url=http://www.ziare.com/viata-sanatoasa/medicina/marijuana-medicinala-e-legala-in-romania-de-ce-nu-avem-pe-piata-niciun-medicament-pe-baza-de-canabis-1427910 |accessdate=24 August 2018 |work=ziare.com |date=6 July 2016}}</ref>

