'''Phyu Phyu Kyaw Thein''' ({{lang-my|ဖြူဖြူကျော်သိန်း}}) is a prominent [[Burmese music|Burmese pop]] singer, known for her stage presence and costumes.<ref name="yym">{{cite news|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/special-features/161-youth-2013/4227-myanmar-s-darling-of-pop-phyu-phyu-kyaw-thein.html|title=Myanmar’s darling of pop, Phyu Phyu Kyaw Thein|last=Yu Yu Maw|date=25 February 2013|accessdate=18 July 2015}}</ref> She has been a [[UNICEF]] celebrity ambassador since 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unicef.org/myanmar/partners_3492.html|title=Phyu Phyu Kyaw Thein|work=UNICEF|accessdate=18 July 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722215309/http://www.unicef.org/myanmar/partners_3492.html|archivedate=22 July 2015|df=}}</ref><ref name="yym"/>
Phyu Phyu Kyaw Thein is a [[physician]] by training; she graduated from the [[University of Medicine 1, Yangon]].<ref name="zpp">{{cite news|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/lifestyle/14046-blown-cover.html|title=Blown cover|last=Zon Pann Pwint|date=10 April 2015|work=Myanmar Times|accessdate=18 July 2015}}</ref> She debuted in 2003 with the album ''Not Concerned Anymore'' ({{my|လုံးဝမသက်ဆိုင်တော့ပါ}}).<ref name="nb">{{cite news|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/lifestyle/2350-singer-expands-her-repertoire-of-covers.html|title=Singer expands her repertoire of covers|last=Nuam Bawi|date=25 July 2011|work=Myanmar Times|accessdate=18 July 2015}}</ref>
