The '''School of Health in Social Science''' at the [[University of Edinburgh]] is a department undertaking research and teaching into health, [[health policy]] and related fields. It is part of the College of Arts, Humanities and Social Sciences.

The school offers postgraduate degrees in [[Clinical Psychology]], [[Counselling]] and [[Psychotherapy]], [[Dementia]], Health and Social Care and [[University of Edinburgh Nursing Studies Programme|Nursing Studies]], together with an undergraduate honours degree in Nursing (Bachelor of Nursing with Honours).<ref>{{cite web|title=About the School of Health in Social Science|url=http://www.ed.ac.uk/schools-departments/health/about|publisher=University of Edinburgh|accessdate=2 August 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Research at the School of Health in Social Science|url=http://www.ed.ac.uk/schools-departments/health/research|publisher=University of Edinburgh|accessdate=2 August 2012}}</ref>

